column1: # Strategy 1 = calculate withdrawal at start and keep const
# Strategy 2 = calculate withdrawal as percentage of current
# Strategy 3 = calculate withdrawal as given percentage from the average of 3 prior years
# Cycles = how many steps in each experiment. 1 year = 10.86 steps
# Repeat = how many times repeat each experiment
# Withdrawal = how many % to take out each YEAR (we assume that year = 11 steps
# Rebalance = Period: rebalance each x steps. 0 means no rebalance.
